4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT ALLOWING A LOCAL FIRST RESPONDER ENTITY TO
5 ESTABLISH A PEER SUPPORT PROGRAM; PROVIDING FOR MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS OF A LOCAL
6 FIRST RESPONDER PEER SUPPORT PROGRAM; AND PROHIBITING A QUALIFIED PEER SUPPORTER
7 FROM TESTIFYING ABOUT THE CONTENT OF A PEER SUPPORT SESSION.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Local first responder peer support programs. (1) A police department,
12 sheriff's office, fire department, or emergency medical service provider may establish a first responder peer
13 support program that is in compliance with the provisions of this section.
14 (2) A local first responder peer support program must have a written policy that outlines, at a
15 minimum:
16 (a) qualifications for a peer supporter, including certification and continuing education
17 requirements;
18 (b) guidelines for what constitutes a peer support session from a conversation between peers;
19 (c) definitions for a group debrief and peer support team;
20 (d) the prohibition of recording in writing or by video or audio any peer support session;
21 (e) how peer supporters in the program shall comply with the Health Insurance Portability and
22 Accountability Act of 1996, 42 U.S.C. 1320d, et seq.;
23 (f) the ability of an employee to use multiple peer supporters;
24 (g) the protection of an employee from being forced to use a peer supporter who holds supervisory
25 authority over the employee;
26 (h) the prohibition of harassment or discrimination against an employee or volunteer who seeks
27 services from the peer support program; and
28 (i) confidentiality protections of the peer support program, including the following exceptions:
