1 (i) if the employee has committed or plans to commit a crime; and
2 (ii) if the employee indicates the employee will cause harm to themself or to others.
3 (3) A peer support session is confidential, and a qualified peer supporter in a local first responder
4 peer support program is prohibited from providing testimony about a peer support session, including individual
5 and group peer support sessions.
6
7 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
8 integral part of Title 7, chapter 32, part 21, and the provisions of Title 7, chapter 32, part 21, apply to [section 1].
